00:00:32.990 --> 00:00:35.590 align:middle line:84%
>> NARRATOR: And now, the host
of the nationally syndicated

00:00:35.590 --> 00:00:39.710 align:middle line:84%
"Coast to Coast AM" and Gaiam
TV bring you "Beyond Belief"

00:00:39.710 --> 00:00:40.715 align:middle line:90%
with George Noory.

00:00:40.715 --> 00:00:42.090 align:middle line:84%
>> GEORGE NOORY:
How's everybody?

00:00:42.090 --> 00:00:43.730 align:middle line:90%
And welcome to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:43.730 --> 00:00:47.630 align:middle line:84%
You know, everybody, at
one point in their life,

00:00:47.630 --> 00:00:51.170 align:middle line:84%
wants love, wants
a relationship.

00:00:51.170 --> 00:00:53.350 align:middle line:84%
Well our special guest
tonight on "Beyond Belief,"

00:00:53.350 --> 00:00:56.840 align:middle line:84%
Marla Martenson, author of
"Excuse Me, Your Soul Mate

00:00:56.840 --> 00:01:00.050 align:middle line:84%
is Waiting," she
is a matchmaker.

00:01:00.050 --> 00:01:01.610 align:middle line:90%
Let's welcome Marla Martenson.

00:01:01.610 --> 00:01:03.426 align:middle line:90%
Hey, Marla.

00:01:03.426 --> 00:01:04.290 align:middle line:90%
How are you?

00:01:04.290 --> 00:01:05.160 align:middle line:90%
>> MARLA MARTENSON: Hi, George.

00:01:05.160 --> 00:01:06.266 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Good to see you.

00:01:06.266 --> 00:01:06.760 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Hey, you too.

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:07.160 align:middle line:90%
Thanks.

00:01:07.160 --> 00:01:08.130 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Have a seat.

00:01:08.130 --> 00:01:10.994 align:middle line:90%
So what is a matchmaker?

00:01:10.994 --> 00:01:11.910 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Oh, boy.

00:01:11.910 --> 00:01:13.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, a matchmaker
is someone who

00:01:13.530 --> 00:01:16.380 align:middle line:84%
will facilitate
finding your soul mate,

00:01:16.380 --> 00:01:18.110 align:middle line:90%
or a relationship, really.

00:01:18.110 --> 00:01:20.690 align:middle line:84%
It's, I get a lot
of male clients

00:01:20.690 --> 00:01:22.475 align:middle line:84%
who are CEOs of
companies, they're busy,

00:01:22.475 --> 00:01:23.717 align:middle line:90%
they're traveling around.

00:01:23.717 --> 00:01:25.300 align:middle line:84%
They don't want to
go on the internet.

00:01:25.300 --> 00:01:26.841 align:middle line:84%
They don't want to
hang out at a bar.

00:01:26.841 --> 00:01:28.460 align:middle line:90%
So they say, Marla, you take it.

00:01:28.460 --> 00:01:30.460 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell you what I want, and
you find me a great quality.

00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:31.260 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: And you go searching.

00:01:31.260 --> 00:01:32.060 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: And I search.

00:01:32.060 --> 00:01:33.620 align:middle line:90%
I'm a-- I'm a real-life cupid.

00:01:33.620 --> 00:01:35.690 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Is it easy to
find the right person,

00:01:35.690 --> 00:01:37.649 align:middle line:90%
to match up the right people?

00:01:37.649 --> 00:01:39.690 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: You know,
I get people emailing me,

00:01:39.690 --> 00:01:42.170 align:middle line:84%
sometimes women who say, oh,
I'd love to be a matchmaker.

00:01:42.170 --> 00:01:43.070 align:middle line:90%
Can I work with you?

00:01:43.070 --> 00:01:44.540 align:middle line:90%
Or can you be my mentor?

00:01:44.540 --> 00:01:46.680 align:middle line:84%
It looks so easy,
and so much fun.

00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:47.670 align:middle line:90%
Well, it is fun.

00:01:47.670 --> 00:01:51.250 align:middle line:84%
It's not always easy, because
people have their lists,

00:01:51.250 --> 00:01:53.450 align:middle line:84%
you know, of what they
want in a perfect person.

00:01:53.450 --> 00:01:56.290 align:middle line:84%
And when they're paying for
someone to find it for them,

00:01:56.290 --> 00:01:58.320 align:middle line:84%
they really expect you
to deliver, you know?

00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:01.760 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: So if somebody comes
to you as a client and says,

00:02:01.760 --> 00:02:05.790 align:middle line:84%
I want to find the
ideal mate for me,

00:02:05.790 --> 00:02:10.096 align:middle line:84%
how many people do they normally
go through before they find

00:02:10.096 --> 00:02:11.016 align:middle line:90%
that person.

00:02:11.016 --> 00:02:13.182 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: You know,
well, something's very cute.

00:02:13.182 --> 00:02:15.350 align:middle line:84%
I have a new client
now, he's 73.

00:02:15.350 --> 00:02:16.600 align:middle line:90%
He is absolutely adorable.

00:02:16.600 --> 00:02:18.820 align:middle line:84%
And I matched him on his
first match, the other day,

00:02:18.820 --> 00:02:20.300 align:middle line:90%
and they went out to dinner.

00:02:20.300 --> 00:02:22.130 align:middle line:84%
He sent her flowers
on Valentine's Day.

00:02:22.130 --> 00:02:24.080 align:middle line:84%
And he calls me up, he
goes, you're a genius.

00:02:24.080 --> 00:02:26.330 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, I love
starting my day like that.

00:02:26.330 --> 00:02:29.520 align:middle line:84%
So that was nice to hear,
and he was really happy.

00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:31.620 align:middle line:84%
Some people are extremely
picky and, George,

00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:33.969 align:middle line:90%
they might go through 25--

00:02:33.969 --> 00:02:34.510 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: No?

00:02:34.510 --> 00:02:35.510 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: 30 people.

00:02:35.510 --> 00:02:38.680 align:middle line:84%
They might keep-- I have a guy
who's been with me 10 years.

00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:40.999 align:middle line:84%
And he wants something
really specific.

00:02:40.999 --> 00:02:43.040 align:middle line:84%
And I don't think he's
probably going to find it.

00:02:43.040 --> 00:02:43.740 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: 10 years?

00:02:43.740 --> 00:02:44.948 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Yeah, you know.

00:02:44.948 --> 00:02:46.750 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And he
pays his fee, right?

00:02:46.750 --> 00:02:47.280 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: He does.

00:02:47.280 --> 00:02:47.779 align:middle line:90%
He does.

00:02:47.779 --> 00:02:48.720 align:middle line:90%
And he's a great guy.

00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:50.678 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Maybe he doesn't
want a relationship.

00:02:50.678 --> 00:02:51.910 align:middle line:90%
Maybe he's just having fun.

00:02:51.910 --> 00:02:52.310 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:02:52.310 --> 00:02:53.684 align:middle line:84%
People, psychologists
and things,

00:02:53.684 --> 00:02:55.482 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a psychologist
or a psychiatrist.

00:02:55.482 --> 00:02:56.190 align:middle line:90%
I'm just a cupid.

00:02:56.190 --> 00:02:57.937 align:middle line:84%
But people that I
talk to say, people

00:02:57.937 --> 00:02:59.770 align:middle line:84%
like that, they have
blocks, and they really

00:02:59.770 --> 00:03:01.220 align:middle line:84%
don't want to find
a relationship

00:03:01.220 --> 00:03:03.050 align:middle line:90%
and they say they do.

00:03:03.050 --> 00:03:03.750 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:06.630 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And what percent of
the people that you match up

00:03:06.630 --> 00:03:07.955 align:middle line:90%
end up getting married?

00:03:07.955 --> 00:03:09.663 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: I always
get this question.

00:03:09.663 --> 00:03:10.810 align:middle line:90%
What's your success rate?

00:03:10.810 --> 00:03:12.399 align:middle line:84%
In the 10 years I've
been doing this,

00:03:12.399 --> 00:03:13.940 align:middle line:84%
I've had so many
marriages, I've gone

00:03:13.940 --> 00:03:16.630 align:middle line:84%
to a couple really great
weddings, babies being born.

00:03:16.630 --> 00:03:18.820 align:middle line:84%
But I don't have a number,
because sometimes people

00:03:18.820 --> 00:03:20.314 align:middle line:84%
will go off into
the sunset dating,

00:03:20.314 --> 00:03:22.480 align:middle line:84%
and then they get married
and I never know about it.

00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:23.340 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: But it does happen.

00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:24.340 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Oh,
sure it happens.

00:03:24.340 --> 00:03:24.690 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:03:24.690 --> 00:03:25.140 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: And they're happy.

00:03:25.140 --> 00:03:25.700 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:03:25.700 --> 00:03:26.450 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: And off they go.

00:03:26.450 --> 00:03:27.800 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: I have had a
couple people who've gotten

00:03:27.800 --> 00:03:29.640 align:middle line:84%
divorced and came back
for another round.

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:30.690 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Really?

00:03:30.690 --> 00:03:31.370 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: I mean this is--

00:03:31.370 --> 00:03:32.240 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: With
different people, right?

00:03:32.240 --> 00:03:34.360 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: With different
people, because we do have,

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:34.860 align:middle line:90%
what?

00:03:34.860 --> 00:03:36.550 align:middle line:84%
A 50% divorce rate
in this country.

00:03:36.550 --> 00:03:38.127 align:middle line:84%
So of course it's
going to happen.

00:03:38.127 --> 00:03:40.710 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And you know, I wanted
to ask you about that, Marla.

00:03:40.710 --> 00:03:45.650 align:middle line:84%
What is nowadays, with the
pressures of everything,

00:03:45.650 --> 00:03:50.100 align:middle line:84%
family, the economy,
everything, what's

00:03:50.100 --> 00:03:54.402 align:middle line:84%
it like to try to develop
a relationship today?

00:03:54.402 --> 00:03:56.110 align:middle line:84%
Because you know, I'm
thinking of my kids

00:03:56.110 --> 00:03:57.180 align:middle line:90%
and my grandchildren.

00:03:57.180 --> 00:03:59.735 align:middle line:84%
What's it going to
be like for them?

00:03:59.735 --> 00:04:02.110 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Well, now it's
really changed from when I--

00:04:02.110 --> 00:04:03.590 align:middle line:84%
you know, when you
and I were growing up.

00:04:03.590 --> 00:04:05.700 align:middle line:84%
We had our mothers stayed
home, at least mine did.

00:04:05.700 --> 00:04:06.540 align:middle line:90%
Most mothers did.

00:04:06.540 --> 00:04:09.280 align:middle line:84%
You know, there was cookies in
the cookie jar, dinner at 6:00.

00:04:09.280 --> 00:04:12.540 align:middle line:84%
You know, it was really a great
thing to have your mom at home.

00:04:12.540 --> 00:04:14.430 align:middle line:84%
And kind of the
"Leave it To Beaver"

00:04:14.430 --> 00:04:15.810 align:middle line:90%
family and neighborhood.

00:04:15.810 --> 00:04:17.660 align:middle line:84%
But now, most
women have to work.

00:04:17.660 --> 00:04:18.660 align:middle line:90%
We're a partnership.

00:04:18.660 --> 00:04:21.149 align:middle line:84%
So I always say, my husband
and I, we're a team.

00:04:21.149 --> 00:04:23.800 align:middle line:84%
And we always say, you know, we
squabble or anything, we say,

00:04:23.800 --> 00:04:26.240 align:middle line:84%
remember we're a team, and
we're doing this together.

00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:28.650 align:middle line:84%
So that's what couples
really have to do,

00:04:28.650 --> 00:04:30.270 align:middle line:90%
nowadays, most couples.

00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:31.580 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: What about disasters?

00:04:31.580 --> 00:04:33.170 align:middle line:84%
We see things,
and I want to talk

00:04:33.170 --> 00:04:35.100 align:middle line:84%
to a lot about the
internet, Marla.

00:04:35.100 --> 00:04:37.970 align:middle line:84%
But we have a case
going where, I think,

00:04:37.970 --> 00:04:41.950 align:middle line:84%
a woman met somebody
on a dating service

00:04:41.950 --> 00:04:45.010 align:middle line:84%
and she got stabbed
by the individual.

00:04:45.010 --> 00:04:45.970 align:middle line:90%
What happened there?

00:04:45.970 --> 00:04:48.376 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Yeah, that
was-- she's suing Match.com

00:04:48.376 --> 00:04:50.990 align:middle line:90%
because she had dated a man.

00:04:50.990 --> 00:04:52.950 align:middle line:84%
I think they only
went out a few times.

00:04:52.950 --> 00:04:55.100 align:middle line:84%
Known him maybe
eight days or so.

00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:58.450 align:middle line:84%
She broke it off because
she felt something was off.

00:04:58.450 --> 00:05:00.970 align:middle line:84%
And then, I believe, this
is just what I'm remembering

00:05:00.970 --> 00:05:02.790 align:middle line:84%
from what I've seen
on TV and the article,

00:05:02.790 --> 00:05:06.650 align:middle line:84%
that maybe a couple months
later, he comes to her home

00:05:06.650 --> 00:05:08.070 align:middle line:90%
and waits in her garage.

00:05:08.070 --> 00:05:11.170 align:middle line:84%
When she got home, stabbed
her multiple times.

00:05:11.170 --> 00:05:13.219 align:middle line:84%
Ended up in the
hospital, almost died.

00:05:13.219 --> 00:05:15.010 align:middle line:84%
He left her for dead,
thought she was dead.

00:05:15.010 --> 00:05:16.900 align:middle line:84%
And then he left and
went to another state

00:05:16.900 --> 00:05:18.270 align:middle line:90%
and killed another woman.

00:05:18.270 --> 00:05:23.077 align:middle line:90%
And so it was just devastating.

00:05:23.077 --> 00:05:25.660 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: And her contention is
they should be screening these

00:05:25.660 --> 00:05:26.159 align:middle line:90%
people?

00:05:26.159 --> 00:05:27.320 align:middle line:90%
But how do you screen them?

00:05:27.320 --> 00:05:28.170 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: You really can't.

00:05:28.170 --> 00:05:29.300 align:middle line:90%
You have to be-- they can't.

00:05:29.300 --> 00:05:31.425 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's millions
of people on there, right?

00:05:31.425 --> 00:05:33.974 align:middle line:84%
So as a woman, not to
blame the victim at all,

00:05:33.974 --> 00:05:35.890 align:middle line:84%
this is horrible, but
he knew where she lived.

00:05:35.890 --> 00:05:38.064 align:middle line:84%
This was some-- I would
never take a man home.

00:05:38.064 --> 00:05:38.730 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Right.

00:05:38.730 --> 00:05:41.320 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: I would suggest
not to, until you're really--

00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:41.900 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: You're really--

00:05:41.900 --> 00:05:42.941 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: --know him.

00:05:42.941 --> 00:05:44.924 align:middle line:84%
And especially if
you have children.

00:05:44.924 --> 00:05:46.715 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't want them
to know where I lived.

00:05:46.715 --> 00:05:48.550 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: But so these
wacko things do happen?

00:05:48.550 --> 00:05:49.230 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: They can happen.

00:05:49.230 --> 00:05:50.188 align:middle line:90%
You have to be careful.

00:05:50.188 --> 00:05:52.427 align:middle line:84%
Because anybody can get
on there, on the internet.

00:05:52.427 --> 00:05:53.260 align:middle line:90%
But it's great, too.

00:05:53.260 --> 00:05:55.468 align:middle line:84%
I know people who have gotten
married from Match.com.

00:05:55.468 --> 00:05:57.280 align:middle line:90%
It's a great resource.

00:05:57.280 --> 00:05:58.377 align:middle line:90%
So there's good and bad.

00:05:58.377 --> 00:06:00.710 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Well, like you say,
people are trying to avoid

00:06:00.710 --> 00:06:04.370 align:middle line:84%
going into bars and places
to meet other people.

00:06:04.370 --> 00:06:08.690 align:middle line:84%
I mean, with the social
networking the way it is now,

00:06:08.690 --> 00:06:10.860 align:middle line:84%
it's probably easy,
at least, to strike up

00:06:10.860 --> 00:06:12.580 align:middle line:90%
a conversation with people.

00:06:12.580 --> 00:06:16.030 align:middle line:84%
I think of the case of
the Notre Dame linebacker

00:06:16.030 --> 00:06:19.950 align:middle line:84%
who had this love affair going
with a fictitious person.

00:06:19.950 --> 00:06:20.700 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Yes!

00:06:20.700 --> 00:06:22.190 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: How in the
heck does this happen?

00:06:22.190 --> 00:06:23.898 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: You
know, I-- I don't know.

00:06:23.898 --> 00:06:25.960 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, didn't
they Skype or something?

00:06:25.960 --> 00:06:26.885 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: They were
doing everything.

00:06:26.885 --> 00:06:27.690 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: You
know, I don't know.

00:06:27.690 --> 00:06:29.540 align:middle line:84%
And it went on
quite a long time.

00:06:29.540 --> 00:06:31.470 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: I mean I
don't know, to this day,

00:06:31.470 --> 00:06:34.940 align:middle line:84%
if he finally caught on, until
it was too late, or what.

00:06:34.940 --> 00:06:37.199 align:middle line:90%
But--

00:06:37.199 --> 00:06:38.615 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: And
he's a busy guy.

00:06:38.615 --> 00:06:40.370 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Who would be on
the other end doing that?

00:06:40.370 --> 00:06:42.090 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it could have been--
it could have been a guy.

00:06:42.090 --> 00:06:42.880 align:middle line:90%
It could have been anybody.

00:06:42.880 --> 00:06:43.160 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Could
have been a guy.

00:06:43.160 --> 00:06:44.300 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, exactly.

00:06:44.300 --> 00:06:44.800 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:46.560 align:middle line:84%
And that's, you know, kind
of, and especially when

00:06:46.560 --> 00:06:48.850 align:middle line:84%
you're in the public, it's
pretty embarrassing, right?

00:06:48.850 --> 00:06:50.475 align:middle line:84%
That he was pretty
embarrassed by that.

00:06:50.475 --> 00:06:52.580 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: But with
today's relationships,

00:06:52.580 --> 00:06:54.190 align:middle line:90%
what are people looking for?

00:06:54.190 --> 00:06:57.940 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Oh, well,
I think it's the same.

00:06:57.940 --> 00:07:00.830 align:middle line:84%
I hear the same for
men and from women.

00:07:00.830 --> 00:07:03.020 align:middle line:84%
Women are looking
for-- the first thing

00:07:03.020 --> 00:07:04.830 align:middle line:84%
that they ask for
is a sense of humor.

00:07:04.830 --> 00:07:07.164 align:middle line:84%
Love a guy with a-- if I
can make a woman laugh,

00:07:07.164 --> 00:07:08.580 align:middle line:84%
she can overlook--
he doesn't need

00:07:08.580 --> 00:07:11.940 align:middle line:84%
to look like Brad Pitt
or George Clooney, right?

00:07:11.940 --> 00:07:14.995 align:middle line:84%
Women, their
specifics tend to be,

