see them anymore,

00:14:30.220 --> 00:14:31.340 align:middle line:90%
because met somewhat special.

00:14:31.340 --> 00:14:31.680 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Wow.

00:14:31.680 --> 00:14:32.070 align:middle line:90%
That's good.

00:14:32.070 --> 00:14:33.060 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: So that's,
yeah, meant a lot.

00:14:33.060 --> 00:14:35.518 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Well, that was also
a classy gesture on his part,

00:14:35.518 --> 00:14:36.370 align:middle line:90%
to let them know.

00:14:36.370 --> 00:14:37.850 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Yeah, to let them
know, instead of just never,

00:14:37.850 --> 00:14:38.780 align:middle line:90%
never calling again.

00:14:38.780 --> 00:14:39.822 align:middle line:90%
You see, guys?

00:14:39.822 --> 00:14:41.530 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Most guys
would just fade away.

00:14:41.530 --> 00:14:42.640 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Because
girls are always saying,

00:14:42.640 --> 00:14:45.150 align:middle line:84%
why do guys say they'll
call, then they never call?

00:14:45.150 --> 00:14:48.140 align:middle line:84%
So that's a big mind
thing for us women.

00:14:48.140 --> 00:14:49.614 align:middle line:90%
We're like, confused.

00:14:49.614 --> 00:14:50.530 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: I love that.

00:14:50.530 --> 00:14:50.870 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:14:50.870 --> 00:14:52.578 align:middle line:84%
Let's take some more
questions for Marla.

00:14:52.578 --> 00:14:55.160 align:middle line:84%
How about from some of
the women in our audience?

00:14:55.160 --> 00:14:56.896 align:middle line:90%
Anybody have a question?

00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.770 align:middle line:84%
>> AUDIENCE: What do
you recommend for the 40

00:14:58.770 --> 00:14:59.430 align:middle line:90%
somethings?

00:14:59.430 --> 00:15:03.010 align:middle line:84%
It seems like an age group
that's kind of neglected.

00:15:03.010 --> 00:15:05.680 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Oh, the
40's are fantastic.

00:15:05.680 --> 00:15:08.099 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, there's no
reason to be neglected.

00:15:08.099 --> 00:15:08.890 align:middle line:90%
Just get out there.

00:15:08.890 --> 00:15:11.260 align:middle line:84%
I have a lot of my men want
to date women in their 40's.

00:15:11.260 --> 00:15:13.593 align:middle line:84%
As long as you're open to
dating a little bit older than

00:15:13.593 --> 00:15:15.485 align:middle line:84%
yourself, if you'll
go up into the 50's.

00:15:15.485 --> 00:15:17.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean the men love the
women in their 40's.

00:15:17.330 --> 00:15:18.190 align:middle line:90%
We still look great.

00:15:18.190 --> 00:15:18.830 align:middle line:90%
We're smart.

00:15:18.830 --> 00:15:19.805 align:middle line:90%
We're confident.

00:15:19.805 --> 00:15:21.800 align:middle line:90%
We feel good in our own skin.

00:15:21.800 --> 00:15:22.970 align:middle line:90%
It's a really great time.

00:15:22.970 --> 00:15:23.900 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: You're more mature.

00:15:23.900 --> 00:15:25.550 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: More mature,
and just do a lot of work

00:15:25.550 --> 00:15:26.050 align:middle line:90%
on yourself.

00:15:26.050 --> 00:15:28.356 align:middle line:84%
I say, always keep
learning and expanding.

00:15:28.356 --> 00:15:29.480 align:middle line:90%
And keep yourself in shape.

00:15:29.480 --> 00:15:30.276 align:middle line:90%
Men are visual.

00:15:30.276 --> 00:15:31.900 align:middle line:84%
A lot of women don't
like to hear this,

00:15:31.900 --> 00:15:33.024 align:middle line:90%
but they are really visual.

00:15:33.024 --> 00:15:35.720 align:middle line:84%
And so if you can keep
yourself healthy, in shape,

00:15:35.720 --> 00:15:37.095 align:middle line:90%
and looking fresh.

00:15:37.095 --> 00:15:39.260 align:middle line:84%
Because that's when we
start to get a little gray.

00:15:39.260 --> 00:15:42.095 align:middle line:84%
And so, keep an updated look
and take care of yourself,

00:15:42.095 --> 00:15:43.855 align:middle line:90%
and there should be no problem.

00:15:43.855 --> 00:15:45.907 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Marla, sometimes
we see mismatches

00:15:45.907 --> 00:15:46.615 align:middle line:90%
in relationships.

00:15:46.615 --> 00:15:49.462 align:middle line:84%
You know, people will look
at a couple and go, whoa!

00:15:49.462 --> 00:15:50.670 align:middle line:90%
What are they doing together?

00:15:50.670 --> 00:15:52.456 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: What's
she doing with him?

00:15:52.456 --> 00:15:55.150 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: And vice versa.

00:15:55.150 --> 00:15:56.800 align:middle line:90%
But how does that happen?

00:15:56.800 --> 00:15:58.490 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what's that attraction?

00:15:58.490 --> 00:16:01.290 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Well, you know,
like for instance, women--

00:16:01.290 --> 00:16:02.820 align:middle line:90%
we love a guy's sense of humor.

00:16:02.820 --> 00:16:06.300 align:middle line:84%
Listen, if he is powerful in
his work, and he's intelligent

00:16:06.300 --> 00:16:09.210 align:middle line:84%
and he's funny, he could
look a little funny.

00:16:09.210 --> 00:16:11.390 align:middle line:90%
And you know, it's sexy.

00:16:11.390 --> 00:16:12.870 align:middle line:84%
So it could look
like a mismatch.

00:16:12.870 --> 00:16:14.530 align:middle line:84%
I mean, remember Dudley
Moore and Susan Anton?

00:16:14.530 --> 00:16:15.140 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Right.

00:16:15.140 --> 00:16:15.900 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Well,
he was adorable.

00:16:15.900 --> 00:16:17.460 align:middle line:84%
But he was like 5,
2 and she was 5,11.

00:16:17.460 --> 00:16:17.900 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Yeah, she was huge.

00:16:17.900 --> 00:16:20.191 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: And people were
like, how does this work?

00:16:20.191 --> 00:16:21.760 align:middle line:84%
But it works,
because these people

00:16:21.760 --> 00:16:23.540 align:middle line:90%
are looking for qualities.

00:16:23.540 --> 00:16:25.410 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: That's because he had
a step stool wherever he went.

00:16:25.410 --> 00:16:26.070 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: He
had a step stool.

00:16:26.070 --> 00:16:28.090 align:middle line:84%
He had a little step ladder
he carried in his back pocket.

00:16:28.090 --> 00:16:29.298 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: How about one more?

00:16:29.298 --> 00:16:31.970 align:middle line:84%
One more question for Marla,
here, before we continue.

00:16:31.970 --> 00:16:33.420 align:middle line:84%
>> AUDIENCE: So
in Beverly Hills,

00:16:33.420 --> 00:16:37.960 align:middle line:84%
it can be a little materialistic
and/or like self-serving.

00:16:37.960 --> 00:16:39.710 align:middle line:84%
Do you ever have to
talk to your clients

00:16:39.710 --> 00:16:43.270 align:middle line:84%
and say, hey, a relationship is
about helping the other person

00:16:43.270 --> 00:16:45.487 align:middle line:84%
and doing right by them,
and not being selfish?

00:16:45.487 --> 00:16:47.570 align:middle line:84%
Have you had to kind of
correct them and say, hey,

00:16:47.570 --> 00:16:48.992 align:middle line:84%
your expectations
are unrealistic?

00:16:48.992 --> 00:16:50.700 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: I give
some great question.

00:16:50.700 --> 00:16:51.575 align:middle line:90%
I give some coaching.

00:16:51.575 --> 00:16:54.352 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I have had women come
in and say-- I had one woman,

00:16:54.352 --> 00:16:55.560 align:middle line:90%
she was probably in her 50's.

00:16:55.560 --> 00:16:58.590 align:middle line:84%
She comes in and she says, I
want to meet a billionaire.

00:16:58.590 --> 00:16:59.882 align:middle line:90%
And she was absolutely adamant.

00:16:59.882 --> 00:17:01.464 align:middle line:84%
I says, you know,
well, for one thing,

00:17:01.464 --> 00:17:03.390 align:middle line:84%
I don't have any
billionaires in my roster.

00:17:03.390 --> 00:17:06.890 align:middle line:84%
And so people will
get caught up in that,

00:17:06.890 --> 00:17:08.750 align:middle line:84%
because you see a
lot of it out there.

00:17:08.750 --> 00:17:12.050 align:middle line:84%
And so I have to remind
them, just because a man is

00:17:12.050 --> 00:17:15.084 align:middle line:84%
jet-setting around, these
guys have this lifestyle

00:17:15.084 --> 00:17:17.500 align:middle line:84%
where they can date the most
exquisite women in the world.

00:17:17.500 --> 00:17:20.240 align:middle line:84%
You see these guys are
dating the top models, right?

00:17:20.240 --> 00:17:23.700 align:middle line:84%
And so if you want to
compete with that, good luck.

00:17:23.700 --> 00:17:27.119 align:middle line:84%
And they change, you know,
they, what do you call it?

00:17:27.119 --> 00:17:28.467 align:middle line:90%
Go up.

00:17:28.467 --> 00:17:29.300 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: The guy's?

00:17:29.300 --> 00:17:30.390 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON:
Yeah, you trade up.

00:17:30.390 --> 00:17:31.190 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Upscale?

00:17:31.190 --> 00:17:33.520 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Upscale, upgrade.

00:17:33.520 --> 00:17:35.600 align:middle line:84%
You know, they could
date whoever they want.

00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:37.950 align:middle line:84%
It's really, it would be a
really stressful situation,

00:17:37.950 --> 00:17:40.280 align:middle line:84%
I think, to date
a guy like that.

00:17:40.280 --> 00:17:41.459 align:middle line:90%
They're traveling a lot.

00:17:41.459 --> 00:17:43.750 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Well, and they
might not be interested in one

00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:44.550 align:middle line:90%
person.

00:17:44.550 --> 00:17:45.450 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: That's
what I'm saying.

00:17:45.450 --> 00:17:46.430 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: They may not be
interested in a relationship.

00:17:46.430 --> 00:17:46.840 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:17:46.840 --> 00:17:48.710 align:middle line:84%
You want somebody who
is going to be there

00:17:48.710 --> 00:17:50.810 align:middle line:84%
when times are rough,
to grow old with.

00:17:50.810 --> 00:17:51.790 align:middle line:90%
What if you get sick?

00:17:51.790 --> 00:17:53.235 align:middle line:84%
What if you lose
an arm or a leg?

00:17:53.235 --> 00:17:54.110 align:middle line:90%
You know what I mean?

00:17:54.110 --> 00:17:56.151 align:middle line:84%
Are they going to leave
you if something happens?

00:17:56.151 --> 00:17:59.130 align:middle line:84%
So what I would
really look for are

00:17:59.130 --> 00:18:00.870 align:middle line:84%
qualities, characters
in a person.

00:18:00.870 --> 00:18:02.570 align:middle line:84%
Of course, you want
to be attracted.

00:18:02.570 --> 00:18:03.800 align:middle line:90%
Everybody does.

00:18:03.800 --> 00:18:07.425 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Is the institution
of a relationship passe?

00:18:07.425 --> 00:18:08.912 align:middle line:90%
Or is it still there?

00:18:08.912 --> 00:18:10.620 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: You
know, it's still there.

00:18:10.620 --> 00:18:12.690 align:middle line:84%
I know a lot more people
are living together,

00:18:12.690 --> 00:18:14.050 align:middle line:90%
not getting married.

00:18:14.050 --> 00:18:17.030 align:middle line:84%
But I think, still,
women, we grew up

00:18:17.030 --> 00:18:19.084 align:middle line:90%
with that fairy tale idea.

00:18:19.084 --> 00:18:20.500 align:middle line:84%
When I was little
girl, I remember

00:18:20.500 --> 00:18:21.710 align:middle line:90%
reading about Cinderella.

00:18:21.710 --> 00:18:23.650 align:middle line:84%
And I used to even
pretend I was a princess.

00:18:23.650 --> 00:18:26.670 align:middle line:84%
Oh, Prince Charming's going
to ride up on his white horse.

00:18:26.670 --> 00:18:29.450 align:middle line:84%
And we still kind of
think that, today.

00:18:29.450 --> 00:18:32.442 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that's where
that, we call it "shallowness"

00:18:32.442 --> 00:18:33.900 align:middle line:84%
comes in, thinking
somebody's going

00:18:33.900 --> 00:18:35.890 align:middle line:84%
to swoop in and save
us or take care of us.

00:18:35.890 --> 00:18:38.660 align:middle line:84%
Or he's going to
look like a prince.

00:18:38.660 --> 00:18:42.030 align:middle line:84%
And it's just really,
it's really a fairy tale.

00:18:42.030 --> 00:18:43.370 align:middle line:90%
The romantic comedies, too.

00:18:43.370 --> 00:18:44.310 align:middle line:90%
They feed into that.

00:18:44.310 --> 00:18:45.851 align:middle line:84%
I always thought,
oh, the perfect guy

00:18:45.851 --> 00:18:48.260 align:middle line:84%
would be Tom Hanks
in "You've Got Mail."

00:18:48.260 --> 00:18:48.870 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:18:48.870 --> 00:18:51.029 align:middle line:84%
But no, that's just
a scripted movie.

00:18:51.029 --> 00:18:51.570 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: OK.

00:18:51.570 --> 00:18:55.510 align:middle line:84%
So you showed us how
you screen your clients.

00:18:55.510 --> 00:18:58.019 align:middle line:84%
How do you screen the
prospective woman?

00:18:58.019 --> 00:18:59.810 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Well,
the women the same way.

00:18:59.810 --> 00:19:03.790 align:middle line:84%
I meet the women, and I talk
to them, get to know them.

00:19:03.790 --> 00:19:05.429 align:middle line:84%
Over the years,
you know, the women

00:19:05.429 --> 00:19:07.720 align:middle line:84%
feel like they're friends,
that we're friends together.

00:19:07.720 --> 00:19:09.760 align:middle line:84%
And then I get feedback
after each date.

00:19:09.760 --> 00:19:11.540 align:middle line:84%
So if a woman
misbehaves, let's say,

00:19:11.540 --> 00:19:14.080 align:middle line:84%
she orders a $500 bottle
of wine on the first date.

00:19:14.080 --> 00:19:14.960 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: He tells
you about that.

00:19:14.960 --> 00:19:15.760 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: He
tells me about it.

00:19:15.760 --> 00:19:17.300 align:middle line:90%
And it's like adios, you know?

00:19:17.300 --> 00:19:18.760 align:middle line:90%
No more matches for you.

00:19:18.760 --> 00:19:20.010 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: Do you dump them?

00:19:20.010 --> 00:19:20.890 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:19:20.890 --> 00:19:21.410 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:19:21.410 --> 00:19:22.459 align:middle line:90%
That's inappropriate.

00:19:22.459 --> 00:19:23.000 align:middle line:90%
>> NOORY: OK.

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:27.210 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Or if somebody
does something like that,

00:19:27.210 --> 00:19:28.030 align:middle line:90%
I can coach them.

00:19:28.030 --> 00:19:30.872 align:middle line:84%
If they apologize and say,
OK, that was out of line.

00:19:30.872 --> 00:19:32.330 align:middle line:84%
You know, I might
match them again.

00:19:32.330 --> 00:19:33.976 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: But it's still
inside of them, isn't it?

00:19:33.976 --> 00:19:35.690 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Yeah, if that's
their character, you know?

00:19:35.690 --> 00:19:37.400 align:middle line:84%
And I really care
about my clients.

00:19:37.400 --> 00:19:39.050 align:middle line:84%
I want them to find
the right person.

00:19:39.050 --> 00:19:41.350 align:middle line:84%
And if that's going on,
that's just such a sense

00:19:41.350 --> 00:19:42.510 align:middle line:90%
of entitlement.

00:19:42.510 --> 00:19:45.230 align:middle line:84%
And like you said,
it's just rude.

00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:47.130 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Are people
scammed sometimes?

00:19:47.130 --> 00:19:50.730 align:middle line:84%
I mean, do you have someone
who comes in and tricks you,

00:19:50.730 --> 00:19:52.100 align:middle line:90%
or tries to?

00:19:52.100 --> 00:19:55.597 align:middle line:84%
Some guy who isn't
who he says he is?

00:19:55.597 --> 00:19:57.930 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Thank goodness,
I haven't had that happen.

00:19:57.930 --> 00:20:00.112 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times, I
go to my clients' homes.

00:20:00.112 --> 00:20:01.570 align:middle line:84%
I love to meet them
at their house,

00:20:01.570 --> 00:20:03.260 align:middle line:84%
because I like to see
how-- I can tell the women,

00:20:03.260 --> 00:20:04.176 align:middle line:90%
I've been to his home.

00:20:04.176 --> 00:20:05.640 align:middle line:90%
It's beautifully decorated.

00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:07.200 align:middle line:84%
Or he takes me to
lunch or dinner,

00:20:07.200 --> 00:20:09.140 align:middle line:84%
so I kind of see
how they interact.

00:20:09.140 --> 00:20:11.730 align:middle line:84%
And when they're paying that
kind of money for a matchmaker,

00:20:11.730 --> 00:20:13.865 align:middle line:84%
they pretty much are
who they say they are.

00:20:13.865 --> 00:20:15.990 align:middle line:84%
On the internet, it could
be a little more sketchy.

00:20:15.990 --> 00:20:17.410 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: Right,
I would think so.

00:20:17.410 --> 00:20:18.620 align:middle line:84%
A little bit later
on, we're going

00:20:18.620 --> 00:20:20.820 align:middle line:84%
to pick somebody out of the
audience and do an example.

00:20:20.820 --> 00:20:21.695 align:middle line:90%
>> MARTENSON: Oh, OK.

00:20:21.695 --> 00:20:23.470 align:middle line:84%
>> NOORY: That's
to-- that we do that.

00:20:23.470 --> 00:20:25.330 align:middle line:84%
What would you
recommend to people

00:20:25.330 --> 00:20:28.620 align:middle line:84%
right now who are not
going through matchmaking,

00:20:28.620 --> 00:20:30.884 align:middle line:90%
who might not be able to?

00:20:30.884 --> 00:20:32.300 align:middle line:84%
How do they meet
the right person?

00:20:32.300 --> 00:20:33.320 align:middle line:90%
What do they do?

00:20:33.320 --> 00:20:34.580 align:middle line:84%
>> MARTENSON: Well,
you know what I love?

00:20:34.580 --> 00:20:35.871 align:middle line:90%
I always talk about meetup.com.

00:20:35.871 --> 00:20:38.270 align:middle line:84%
And I know, I think,
in the states,

00:20:38.270 --> 00:20:41.605 align:middle line:84%
they are in pretty much
every state, meetup.com.

00:20:41.605 --> 00:20:44.360 align:middle line:84%
They have all sorts
of groups, Meet Ups,

00:20:44.360 --> 00:20:47.240 align:middle line:84%
where if you like hiking, if
you're a book club, into wine

00:20:47.240 --> 00:20:49.300 align:middle line:84%
tastings, want to
learn another language.

00:20:49.300 --> 00:20:51.550 align:middle line:84%
Anything you want to do,
they've got a Meet Up for it.

00:20:51.550 --> 00:20:53.580 align:middle line:84%
